question: In which of the following sequences the change in quantity of money leads to change in price level in the Keynesian models?
option1: Change in quantity of money - change in investment - change in employment and output - change in rate of interest - change in price level
option2: Change in quantity of money - change in employment and output - change in investment - change in the rate of interest - change in price level
option3: Change in quantity of money - change in investment - change in rate of interest - change in employment and output - change in price level
option4: Change in quantity of money - change in rate of interest - change in investment - change in employment and output - change in price level
answer: Change in quantity of money - change in rate of interest - change in investment - change in employment and output - change in price level
